        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-11-08 19:11:48.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n@Parshad, changing from [a-z]* to *, is this change meant to remove all the files under web apps, so that the default page is also removed and by which you achieve disabling portal-app default page?\n\nTrying understand how it the default page is disabled.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "9d06dc50e4a3d0f89daedb83a32975fa88184789",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 2493,
          "name": "Parshad Ramniklal Patel",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "pars.patel@samsung.com",
          "username": "Pars"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-11-09 00:19:06.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> @Parshad, changing from [a-z]* to *, is this change meant to remove\n > all the files under web apps, so that the default page is also\n > removed and by which you achieve disabling portal-app default page?\n > \n > Trying understand how it the default page is disabled.\n\nYes, by default ROOT web app comes along with Tomcat installation. As mentioned in this issue jira portal-303, this default web app reveals tomcat version and other related information and its accessible via http://portal.api.simpledemo.onap.org:8989/ or http://ip:30215/ url.\n\nRemove command with [a-z]* is not deleting this default web app ROOT, so I changed it to * which will delete all default web apps and will prevent opening of default tomcat page on accessing of http://portal.api.simpledemo.onap.org:8989/ or http://ip:30215/ url.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
